        <section>
          <code code="11506-3" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" codeSystemName="LOINC" displayName="Progress Notes" />
          <title>PROGRESS NOTES</title>
          <text>
            <table xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
              <thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Provider</th><th>Note Type</th><th>Note Text</th><th>Location</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>03/08/2026</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Progress Note</td><td>CC: Chronic pain follow-up, depression check, weight management
HPI: 46yo female with fibromyalgia, chronic back pain, depression, obesity. Reports pain levels 6/10 average (improved from 8/10). Duloxetine helping mood and pain. Gabapentin TID providing some relief. Migraines reduced to 2x/month from weekly since adding topiramate. Weight down 5 lbs (210 from 215).
PHQ-9: 12 (moderate depression — improved from 16). GAD-7: 10 (moderate anxiety).
Pain Assessment: Widespread musculoskeletal pain. Worst in lower back and shoulders. Morning stiffness 45 minutes. Poor sleep quality.
PE: Tender points positive 14/18 (fibromyalgia). Lumbar ROM reduced. No radiculopathy. Straight leg raise negative bilaterally.
Assessment:
# Fibromyalgia (M79.7): Improving. Continue duloxetine + gabapentin.
# Chronic low back pain (M54.5): Stable. Continue PT. No opioids.
# Depression (F33.1): PHQ-9 improving. Continue duloxetine 60mg. Therapy ongoing.
# Obesity (E66.01): Lost 5 lbs. Continue dietary counseling. Consider GLP-1 agonist.
# Prediabetes (R73.03): A1c 5.8% — borderline. Weight loss is key intervention.
# Vitamin D deficiency: Level 18 — increase to 5000 IU daily. Recheck 3 months.
# Migraine (G43.009): Improved on topiramate. Continue.

Care Gaps: Flu vaccine overdue. COVID booster overdue. Tdap overdue (last 2015 — 11 years). Mammogram not done since 2023. Cervical screen due.

Plan: Continue all meds. Order mammogram. Schedule Pap. Administer flu and COVID vaccines today. Tdap at next visit. Labs in 3 months. PT continue. Follow-up 3 months.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
                <tr><td>12/01/2025</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Progress Note</td><td>CC: Worsening depression, pain flare
HPI: Reports increased stress with holiday season and custody issues. PHQ-9 = 16 (moderately severe). Pain 8/10. Not sleeping.
Assessment: Depression worsening, pain flare.
Plan: Increase duloxetine to 60mg (from 30mg). Add cyclobenzaprine 10mg QHS for muscle spasm. Urgent therapy appointment scheduled. If not improving in 2 weeks, consider psychiatric referral. Safety plan reviewed — denies SI/HI.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
                <tr><td>06/01/2025</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Progress Note</td><td>CC: New complaint of fatigue, weight gain, joint pain
HPI: 45yo female with chronic pain reports new onset fatigue worse than usual, weight up 10 lbs in 3 months, diffuse joint pain and morning stiffness. Concerned about autoimmune disease.
Labs ordered: CBC, CMP, TSH, ESR, CRP, ANA, RF, Vitamin D, Iron studies, A1c
Results: TSH 4.8 (upper normal), Vitamin D 18 (low), Ferritin 15 (low), ESR 35 (elevated), CRP 2.8 (elevated), ANA negative, RF negative, A1c 5.8% (prediabetes).
Assessment:
# Prediabetes (R73.03): New diagnosis. Lifestyle modification.
# Vitamin D deficiency (E55.9): Start supplementation.
# Iron deficiency without anemia (E61.1): Low ferritin. Start iron.
# Elevated inflammatory markers: No autoimmune etiology identified. Likely related to obesity/fibromyalgia.
Plan: Start Vitamin D 5000 IU, ferrous sulfate 325mg daily. Dietary counseling. Recheck labs 3 months.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </text>
        </section>
